390 SECTION 2-1005.
391 Mayor and councilmembers; terms; qualifications.
392 The mayor and councilmembers serving on the effective date of this charter shall serve until
393 the expiration of the terms for which each was elected. Their successors shall be elected at
394 the municipal election immediately preceding expiration of such term. The mayor and
395 members of the city council shall serve for terms of four years and until their respective
396 successors are elected and qualified. No person shall be eligible to serve as mayor or
397 councilmember unless that person shall have been a resident of the city for 12 months prior
398 to the date of election. The mayor and each councilmember shall continue to reside within
399 the city during the term for which elected and continue to be registered and qualified to vote
400 in municipal elections of this city and each councilmember shall continue to reside within
401 the district that such member represents during that member's period of service. No person
402 shall be eligible to hold office of mayor or councilmember if convicted of any crime
403 involving moral turpitude. No person shall be eligible to hold the office of mayor or
404 councilman until having passed his or her 21st birthday.
